<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,356,594]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,428,453]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[352,521,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Size and shape</emphasis>
—Test moderately large, 44.7–57.0 mm TL; elongated outline, TW 85–92% TL; strongly inflated, TH 60–71% TL, with widest point coinciding with tip of posterior petals; posterior margin pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,356,594]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[199,354,535,560]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Apical system</emphasis>
—Monobasal, with four gonopores; situated anterior of centre, 29–34% TL from anterior margin of test.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1114,1861,1884]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617493/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" startId="23.[151,250,1861,1883]" targetBox="[151,1436,653,1831]" targetPageId="23">
